<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/532498-i-ve-read-one-catton-civil-war-trilogy">I&#39;ve read one Catton Civil War Trilogy. Are there two? I have the option to read and review this book, but if it is the same as the middle volume of the trilogy I have already read, then there&#39;s not a lot of point in my rereading it.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_532498'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F770515.Glory_Road">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/532498-i-ve-read-one-catton-civil-war-trilogy">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/532498-i-ve-read-one-catton-civil-war-trilogy">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/18688312-gerry"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1488530482i/18688312._UY100_CR7,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/18688312-gerry">Gerry</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">One trilogy concerns itself about the Army of the Potomac: Mr. Lincoln&apos;s Army, Glory Road, and A Stillness at Appomattox. <br/><br/>The other trilogy is about t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">One trilogy concerns itself about the Army of the Potomac: Mr. Lincoln's Army, Glory Road, and A Stillness at Appomattox. <br /><br />The other trilogy is about the whole war: The Coming Fury, Terrible Swift Sword, and Never Call Retreat.<br /><br />He also finished one on U.S. Grant: Captain Sam Grant (by Lloyd Lewis), Grant Moves South, and Grant Takes Command (these two by Catton).<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
