        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer430527046" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15673184685641585668">An interesting history of the Union army prior to Grant. Starting right after McCelland and taking in the failed generals. Very good discussion of the un-unioned part of the northern union. Indiana in particular. Good mind expanding book. <br/><br/>The description of the major battles is detailed, and I learned a LOT regarding the tactics and sometimes the lack of them. The book ends with Lincoln&apos;s Gettysberg Address just about to be given, but doesn&apos;t actually contain the text of the address. I wish that</span>
  <span id="freeText15673184685641585668" style="display:none">An interesting history of the Union army prior to Grant. Starting right after McCelland and taking in the failed generals. Very good discussion of the un-unioned part of the northern union. Indiana in particular. Good mind expanding book. <br /><br />The description of the major battles is detailed, and I learned a LOT regarding the tactics and sometimes the lack of them. The book ends with Lincoln's Gettysberg Address just about to be given, but doesn't actually contain the text of the address. I wish that was included as it would have been a fitting end to 60 pages of detailed battle and body counts.<br /><br />I see why this series is considered the definitive Civil War description. </span>
