<span id="freeTextContainer603994310099482660"><strong>Army of the Potomac</strong><br/><br/>This historical work deals with the Army of the Potomac between the battles of Fredericksburg to Gettysburg. It deals primarily with the inept Union generals but there are glimpses of the view of the common soldier. Easily readable, the Kindle edition suffers from a complete lack of maps which seriously detracts from one’s ability to understand the battle as it unfolds. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


