<div id="review_2249161722" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2249161722" />
    <a title="Bobsie67" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1102847-bobsie67"><img alt="Bobsie67" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1214838737p2/1102847.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2249161722?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bobsie67" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bobsie67" href="/user/show/1102847-bobsie67">Bobsie67</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=american-civil-war">american-civil-war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=five-star-favorites">five-star-favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2249161722" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6958981761990188804">Catton&apos;s anger over the Army of the Potomac&apos;s abysmal leadership is so visceral. He lets us know that it is okay for us too to be angry about the fiascos and follies that led to needles deaths of thousands. His writing is so eloquent. His rendering of Lew Armistead valiant, but doomed, march toward the high-water mark of the Confederacy on the last day of the last battle at Gettysburg had me sobbing, and I&apos;m am no fan of the Lost Cause, and I&apos;m a battle-hardened veteran of dozens of civil war hi</span>
  <span id="freeText6958981761990188804" style="display:none">Catton's anger over the Army of the Potomac's abysmal leadership is so visceral. He lets us know that it is okay for us too to be angry about the fiascos and follies that led to needles deaths of thousands. His writing is so eloquent. His rendering of Lew Armistead valiant, but doomed, march toward the high-water mark of the Confederacy on the last day of the last battle at Gettysburg had me sobbing, and I'm am no fan of the Lost Cause, and I'm a battle-hardened veteran of dozens of civil war histories. Only Foote comes close to the grandeur of Catton's prose.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6958981761990188804" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


